  "text": "GlyRs are most likely to be extrasynaptic [CITATION_1] . In humans, the gene encoding for α4 is a pseudogene and is not expressed [CITATION_2] , but all other subunits were found to be expressed in several brain regions including the cerebral cortex [CITATION_3] , the striatum [CITATION_4] and the amygdala [CITATION_5] .",
